Year = {2024},
Pages = {282-299},
Abstract = {This study presents a conceptual analysis of the role of artificial
   intelligence (AI) in skilling, upskilling, and reskilling the workforce.
   The chapter argues that artificial intelligence (AI) is fundamentally
   reshaping the workforce landscape and necessitating new strategies for
   employee skill development. This paper examines the impact of artificial
   intelligence (AI) on workforce development by synthesizing insights from
   the existing literature. The authors identified the trends, challenges,
   and opportunities of using artificial intelligence in workforce
   development. Informed decision-making and policy formulation in the
   realms of labour and employment contribute to this chapter. In
   conclusion, AI has the potential to transform the future of work and
   redefine the skill sets required for success in an increasingly
