Year = {2019},
Volume = {24},
Number = {1},
Pages = {67-80},
Month = {JUN},
Abstract = {This article presents three important dimensions to consider when
   analyzing the professional integration performance of professional
   graduates: the diversity and professionalization nature of young
   people's pathways upstream of their diploma, the selectivity of
   professional education courses and the types of labor market covered by
   these degrees. Although not related to the quality of the education
   provided, these three dimensions can explain much of the ``good
   results{''} of a professional degree. This leads us to be very cautious
   about the evaluation of a professional degree through its insertion
   performance.},
